Bangchak Plans to Invest $1.64 Billion for Solar Expansion, Post Reports

-- B y   A n u c h i t   N g u y e n
-- 
2011-05-27T00:32:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-27/bangchak-plans-to-invest-1-64-billion-for-solar-expansion-post-reports.html
Bangchak Petroleum Pcl (BCP) , a Thai state-
controlled refiner, plans to spend about 50 billion baht ($1.64
billion) on solar power plant project, Bangkok Post reported,
citing President Anusorn Sangnimnuan.  Click here for web link  To contact the reporter on this story:
